A crew of a private ambulance service in Port Elizabeth wear personal protective equipment (PPE), on July 11, 2020 ahead of checking on a patient affected by COVID-19 coronavirus at her home. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's COVID-19 edges closer to 300,00. 10, 496 new COVID-19 cases have been reported bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 298,292. There has been 174 coronavirus related deaths in the last 24-hours. READ: Mantashe, wife test positive for COVID-19 Gauteng accounts for 82 of the deaths, Northern Cape (4), KwaZulu Natal (27), Eastern Cape (17) and Western Cape (44). This brings the total number of COVID-19 related deaths to 4,346 - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.